England international Kalvin Phillips is being considered by Manchester City, while Erik Ten Hag is said to be seeking a reunion with one of his defensive stars from Ajax in the latest Premier League transfer rumours from the media. Other reports say the new Man United manager, Eric ten Hag, has set his sights on making N'Golo Kante his first signing. Paris St-Germain are getting ready to move for Liverpool's Senegal forward Sadio Mane, 30, amid reports he is stalling on a new contract. Manchester United and France midfielder Paul Pogba, 29, whose contract expires this summer is also said to be on the radar of PSG and Juventus. Meanwhile, Chelsea want to sign AC Milan captain and Italy defender Alessio Romagnoli, 27, this summer on a free transfer.